   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred Fifty THE WAY FOR MAN TO RECEIVE LIFE Scripture: Acts 11:18; John 3:16 Confess</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Man needs to confess that his own nature and behavior are corrupt and that he is dead in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Repent Believe Call</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Man needs to call upon the name of the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Subject Two Hundred Fifty-one THE ASSURANCE OF HAVING RECEIVED THIS LIFE Scripture: 2 John 5:10-13 Assurance through God s Word The Word of God is the assurance that a saved one possesses this life.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>If one does not believe what the Word of God says, he is making God a liar.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Our feelings are undependable</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Do not depend on your feelings; depend on the Word of God.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Subject Two Hundred Fifty-two THE PROOF OF HAVING RECEIVED THIS LIFE Scripture: Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>36:26; Titus 3:5; 1 John 3:14 A person is changed psychologically Changed in the feeling of his conscience Changed in temperament Changed in mind Changed in inclination Changed in life Changed in behavior Changed in his whole being</S>
